title: Rebuild roof and reinstall dome skylight.
job_description:
The current roof on the original first floor extension is sagging after the installation of a dome skylight in 2014. The roof is also leaking occasionally. One of the walls is showing a crack caused by the extra weight from the window pushing the rear wall away from the building. 

The roof will need to be rebuilt with extra joist to support the dome window which is to be re installed. There is a possibility of installing the dome in its diamond orientation (rather than parallel) but extra supports will be needed. The cupboard that houses the boiler will need to be extended to the height of the ceiling and the pipes can be concealed in the joists of the new roof. Finally the ceiling and room will have to be redecorated. Materials needed will include basic building materials as well as new tiles (3x3.3m area), joists and sealant for around the window.

title: A Flat Renovation
job_description:
We're not living in the UK at the moment and plan to come back in June. The property is a three-bedroom flat in central London which has been rented out for the past five years. Ideally, the plan would be to redistribute its areas and make better use of the available space. 

We have an architect drawing up the new layout, but will of course need someone to implement it. :)
Here below is something I put together - as a joke really, as I clearly have no idea what I'm doing - but at least all the missing elements are there and it gives you some initial insight into what we would like to do.  http://view.planup.co.uk/id/168386905

So the works would involve taking a coupIe of walls, replacing kitchen and putting in a new utility room, possibly replacing the flooring throughout (it's currently a non-engineered wood floor - pine, very damaged and very creaky), possibly putting in underfloor heating, replacing bathtub in en-suite bathroom with a shower cabin and redecorating throughout.

We pop back to London quite often but not enough to keep a good eye on this, hence we would also need someone to run the whole project for us.

title: Garage conversion
job_description:
Building a single story garage. 
Job to build a single story garage to fit 1 car and provide bicycle storage. An existing garage is to be knocked down and removed. The new garage will be built at the back of the property. 

The job will involve the following: 

Demolition of Existing Garage 
?	Removal of the existing garage flat roof. It should be assumed that this is made of asbestos sheet. This will have to be removed and disposed of safely. 
?	Knocking down of the existing garage structure. Disposal of the brick, doors and wood work in the existing garage 
?	Break up and removal of the existing concrete floor 
?	Laying topsoil down in place of the existing garage floor 

Building new garage 
?	Digging foundations for the new garage 
?	Laying a concrete floor, creating a level internal floor for the new garage 
?	Build walls and roof of the new garage 
?	Fitting new garage door and side door 

Ground-work 
?	Alterations to the small wall on the LHS of the current driveway 
?	Making good the brick-work of the driveway to meet the new boundaries of the garage side and door 

Services 
Ideally, we would like the garage to have power and lights. If this is too costly or disruptive we will exclude this from the build. 
?	Laying of armoured cable connecting new garage to the mains supply for the house 
?	Fitting ceiling lights inside the garage, with internal switch 
?	Fitting 2 x 2-way electrics wall sockets inside the garage 
?	Fitting 1 x 2-way external socket outside garage 

Have used an architect to do the drawing and have applied for a Consent for Lawful Development (planning permission not needed). 

If you are interested in the job, it might be an idea to share the specification and talk about the work. Ideally, we would like to do this work in August. The Demolition and the Build can be separate. 

Architectual plans have been drawn up for this job 
Building Regulations approval has not been applied for yet

title: A House Renovation
job_description:
Loft conversion with ensuite
Repair balustrades on landing
Re plaster hallway as required
Renovate bathroom- remove old, line walls and install 
Remove old window, level sill and install new double glazed window
Level bathroom floor
Remove extra toilet and make good plaster in 2nd bedroom.

1st bedroom repair plasterwork
Back room downstairs-
Convert double existing back window to double glazed patio doors
Knock wall between kitchen and back room, install RSJ
Remove old kitchen
Remove back door and existing windows, brick up existing doorway and install new window
Install fireplace
Install new kitchen cupboards
Make good all plasterwork and under stairs area
Level floor as required
Rip up carpet in front room
Repair plasterwork as required
Re plaster hallway as required
Polish stair boards
The whole house needs painting
New wooden flooring to be installed downstairs
Install deck outside in back garden

I do not have access to a scanner but the following may help:

The width of the house is 4.8 m approx.
The stairs run up across the house roughly under the roof ridge and the loft stairs would have to be above those. The distance  from the edge of the stairs to the back wall, which would form the main area of the loft ( ie have the roof raise to ridge height with a minimal fall to the back) is approx 3.9 m.
It would be desirable to have an area of loft on the other side of the stairs for storage and a small ensuite. This area would be limited by the fall of the roof towards the street and would only extend about 1.5 to 1.8 from the stair edge towards the street.
Below the loft would be the back bedroom and bathroom and under them are a kitchen and dining room. If possible we would like to remove the wall between the kitchen and dining room using an RSJ .

Currently in the roof space there is a water tank that would need to be shifted.

title: An Extension
job_description:
We are buying a property which we intend to do quite a bit of work to. The house is a Victorian mid-terrace, with 3 bedrooms and a 4th attic room which was done about 10 years ago (so isn't an official room). We would like to bring it up to date and make it a beautiful home suitable for a family of 4 (and possibly 5 in the future!)
We would like to;
- Update the attic, add a dormer window/flatten out the ceiling height, and potentially add an additional bedroom and bathroom up there.
- Extend the kitchen into the side return and out into the garden as well creating a large live in kitchen/diner/seating are
- At the same time creating a downstairs cloakroom and utility room 
- add a small en-suite to the front bedroom
- update the main bathroom

Notes:

Will be living there at the same time so need for speed especially with downstairs/kitchen

Kitchen
Please quote for new bricks and also bricks to match existing brickwork
Please quote to leave one internal wall (side return side) as exposed brick
Pitched roof to include 5xvelux Windows
Concrete flooring, screed ready for tiling and cost to lay tiles in whole kitchen space and quote to leave floor as polished concrete
Replace dining room window with smaller opening for floor to ceiling window
Remove existing boiler from top bedroom and fit new boiler system in kitchen.
(Some advice on improving water pressure and best way to do this please would be welcome!)
Create bifold door space opening
Continue flooring to around 2m to rear of extension (creation of patio area)
Mixture of spotlights (x6) and pendant light fittings (x3)
Preference to create step/s down to lower floor as you enter kitchen, then all floor one level out to patio

Create wc underneath stairs space

Bathroom
Remove current bathroom
Reduce size of bathroom, fit new 3 piece bathroom suite (bath, sink unit and toilet)

Loft
Fit new staircase
Fit 2xlight tunnels-1 to front bedroom, 1 to 2nd floor stair well
Fit 4 piece bathroom-separate bath and shower plus wc and sink
Fit radiators in bedrooms, bathroom and hallway
4xspotlights in rear bedroom
2xpendant light fittings to front bedroom
4x bathroom spotlights


General
Skirting boards and architraves to match rest of house style

Additional
Please provide contact names and numbers of 2 recently completed projects that are happy to give references
Please advise on payments schedule
Please call out any contracted work undertaken by others
Length of working day, start & finish times
Availability to start & anticipated length from start to completion
